[normal]unsurfaced
[normal]) routes as Byways will solve the problem. There is already a statutory precedent for such a change, namely the reclassification of all Roads Used as Public Paths 
[normal](RUPPs) as either footpaths or bridleways under the Countryside and Rights of Way Act 2000.
